body: I ran this through Travis without #648 on my repo and it [failed](https://travis-ci.org/robinlinden/c-toxcore/jobs/322627527) as it should have. --- This change is [](https://reviewable.io/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/649)

comment_regular_data.body: So FreeBSD Travis is failing because `MSGPACK_OBJECT_FLOAT32` and `MSGPACK_OBJECT_FLOAT64` don't exist in `msgpack-1.4.2_3`.
@robinlinden the msgpack package in the repos seem to be out of date. I ran into this problem when I was fixing hstox. I compiled msgpack from source and it worked.
So, TODO(@robinlinden): Compile msgpack from source when building on freebsd.

--- Reviewed 1 of 1 files at r1. Review status: all files reviewed at latest revision, all discussions resolved, some commit checks failed. --- *Comments from [Reviewable](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/c-toxcore/649#-:-L2wKf1DaQuIO20dLKQo:b-jbsf8z)*
Don't do the compiling from source. Merge this. We'll see if we can make the next version of the hstox tests work with older versions of msgpack.

So, does the FreeBSD build succeed or fail with this change? If it will always fail due to msgpack being too old, then we won't see if building toxcore without msgpack breaks on FreeBSD -- it would make FreeBSD build quite useless.
It always fails. I'll add building msgpack from source as soon as I have time.
Oh, so the PR is not complete yet, alright then.
We'll want msgpack at some point in the future, but not right now. hstox is gone from the repo.
